West German retail group Kaufhof AG&lt;KFHG.F> is considering taking a stake in shipping andtransport group Hapag-Lloyd AG &lt;HPLG.F> but has yet to reach afinal decision, a spokesman said in response to queries.    Press reports said Kaufhof wanted a stake of up to 12.5 pctin Hapag-Lloyd.    The Kaufhof spokesman noted any decision on purchasingshares in the shipping group would have to be approved by thesupervisory board, which is due to hold a meeting tomorrow.    Late last year the Gevaert group of Belgium and WestGermany's VEBA AG &lt;VEBG.F> said they had each acquired a 12.5pct stake in Hapag-Lloyd from Deutsche Bank AG &lt;DBKG.F> andDresdner Bank AG &lt;DRSD.F>.     Industry sources estimate Deutsche and Dresdner,Hapag-Lloyd's majority shareholders, held about 75 pct ofHapag-Lloyd's share capital before selling portions of it toGevaert and VEBA.    The two banks have said they eventually wanted to reducetheir stake in the shipping group to 15 pct each. REUTER&#3;